    "recap_headline": "Sacred Heart",
    "recap_text": "Hamden, Conn. \u2013\nSacred Heart recorded key hits from\nJacob Schmutz\n,\nRonan Donohue\n,\nWill Rudolph\n, and\nPeter Link\nbut could not close the gap after Quinnipiac's early offensive surge.\nRecords\nSacred Heart | 4-12 (3-3 MAAC)\nQuinnipiac | 5-11 (1-2 MAAC)\nTop Performers\nWill Rudolph\n: 1-4, R, double\nJacob Schmutz\n: 1-4, R, double\nPeter Link\n: 1-2, RBI\nRonan Donohue\n: 1-4, RBI\nGeorge Katsaros\n: 4.0 IP, 2 H, 1 R, 5 SO\nHow It Happened\nQuinnipiac jumped out to an early lead, scoring seven runs in the bottom of the first inning.\nOn the mound,\nGeorge Katsaros\nsettled in after the opening frame, recording two strikeouts in the second inning and two more in the third before adding his fifth strikeout in the fourth.\nSacred Heart got on the board in the fourth inning when\nJacob Schmutz\ndoubled and later scored on a single from\nRonan Donohue\n. Quinnipiac added another run in the sixth before the Pioneers answered in the seventh, as\nWill Rudolph\ndoubled and came around to score on a single from\nPeter Link\n.\nThe Bobcats added two more runs in the bottom of the seventh to extend their lead and end the score 2-10.\nUp Next\nThe Pioneers travel to Chestnut Hill, Mass., to face Boston College on Tuesday, March 17, with first pitch set for 3 p.m."
